    • crossProduct

      @Contract(pure=true) public static float crossProduct(float ax, float ay, float bx, float by)
      Returns the cross product of vector a and vector b.

      a and b form three-dimensional vectors with z-axis value equal to zero. The cross product is a three-dimensional vector with x-axis and y-axis values equal to zero. The cross product z-axis component is returned.

      Returns:
      area spanned by vectors signed by angle direction

    • setLength

      public static boolean setLength(float[] pos, int off, float length)
      Sets vector to (x, y) scaled to length, if possible. If new length is zero or NaN, returns false; otherwise returns true.

      The vector is given by (v[off], v[off+1]), off must be even. length must be >= 0.
